<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFCFFBDFC959D1B6DEF7F58" pageId="17" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFCFFBDFC959D1B6DEE7CD9" blockId="17.[831,1437,351,569]" pageId="17" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFCFFBDFC959D1B6ABD7C16" bold="true" box="[831,944,351,375]" pageId="17" pageNumber="31">Remarks:</emphasis>
The initial stage of this species is planispirally coiled while the later stages are uncoiled. The chambers become elongated and slightly inflated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFCFFBDFC959D846DEF7F58" blockId="17.[831,1437,351,569]" pageId="17" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFCFFBDFC959D846D7B7CB9" bold="true" box="[831,1142,448,472]" pageId="17" pageNumber="31">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is originally described from the Cretaceous of 
<collectingRegion id="8818F811FFFCFFBDFBF09DA56D967C99" box="[1114,1179,481,504]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="17" pageNumber="31">Texas</collectingRegion>
. It is recorded in the Campanian by SLITER (1968). In the study area, it is found in the Late Paleocene sediments.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
